pve-fclu (0.1.0~alpha6) stable; urgency=medium

  * FCMultipath: two fixes found during live E590H data-path testing (activate
    mapped the LUN array-side but the host device never appeared):
    - attach() now rescan_scsi_hosts BEFORE wait_for_device — publish_lu adds the
      LU paths array-side, but the host must rescan its SCSI/FC hosts before
      multipathd can assemble /dev/mapper/3<naa>. Without it activate timed out.
    - detach() is a no-op success when the identity carries no usable device id
      (a volume allocated but never activated), so free_image can still tear it
      down instead of dying on the missing wwid.

 -- Ciro Iriarte <ciro.iriarte+software@gmail.com>  Wed, 01 Jul 2026 16:40:00 -0300

pve-fclu (0.1.0~alpha5) stable; urgency=medium

  * plugin: FIX a showstopper found during the live E590H cutover — the base
    plugin never loaded connector_class / driver_class (vendor-overridable
    strings the base cannot `use` at compile time), so activate/deactivate/
    free/map died with "Can't locate object method new via package
    PVE::Storage::FCLU::Host::FCMultipath". The unit tests missed it because
    they inject fakes for both. _connector/_build_driver now _load_class the
    module first; new regression test drives the REAL base _connector.
  * plugin: report storage APIVER 14 (was clamped to 12), silencing PVE 9.2's
    "implementing an older storage API" warning on every pvesm call.

 -- Ciro Iriarte <ciro.iriarte+software@gmail.com>  Wed, 01 Jul 2026 16:00:00 -0300

pve-fclu (0.1.0~alpha4) stable; urgency=medium

  * hitachi: add the pve-fclu-migrate-hitachi tool + PVE::Storage::FCLU::Migrate::
    Hitachi module to migrate a reference pve-storage-hitachiblock on-disk store
    into the FCLU registry format BEFORE swapping plugins — otherwise the swap
    orphans existing volumes (FCLU::Registry reads /etc/pve/priv/fclu/, the
    reference used /etc/pve/priv/hitachiblock/, and the two packages Conflict so
    they can't coexist). COPY mode: it reads the legacy <storeid>.{json,creds} and
    writes the FCLU store via FCLU::Registry/Credentials (guaranteed format,
    atomic + 0600), never touching the legacy files (rollback safety net) and
    idempotent. Maps ldev_id->backend_id (string), wwid->identity{naa},
    pool_id->pool_ref, clone_snapshot_id/clone_pvol_ldev->clone_backing_snap/
    clone_parent_backend (#23), and the snapshot subregistry. Validated on the
    live lab store (13 volumes incl. a linked clone) in a dry run. See
    docs/migration-hitachi.md. New t/unit/migrate_hitachi.t.

 -- Ciro Iriarte <ciro.iriarte+software@gmail.com>  Wed, 01 Jul 2026 15:00:00 -0300

pve-fclu (0.1.0~alpha3) stable; urgency=medium

  * hitachiblock: wire the persistent_reservations validate-and-warn check into
    activate_volume, so the GUI checkbox / storage.cfg option is no longer
    cosmetic. When enabled, activation now calls the connector's check_pr_ready
    (guarded via can(), so a non-multipath transport skips it) and warns — never
    blocks — with actionable guidance if this node's host-side SCSI-3 PR plumbing
    (qemu-pr-helper socket + a multipath reservation_key) is not ready. Matches
    the property description and mirrors how skip_unmap_io_check is wired. New
    plugin.t coverage for the off / ready / not-ready paths.

 -- Ciro Iriarte <ciro.iriarte+software@gmail.com>  Wed, 01 Jul 2026 13:00:00 -0300

pve-fclu (0.1.0~alpha2) stable; urgency=medium

  * pve-fclu-hitachi: re-ship the web UI + host-side extras dropped in the
    alpha1 rename swap, so the driver package is at parity with the superseded
    pve-storage-hitachiblock for the GUI and PR paths:
    - The ExtJS storage panel (src/www/manager6/hitachiblock.js, served as
      /pve2/js/pve-fclu-hitachi.js): the "Add: Hitachi Block" create/edit dialog
      and the friendly grid label. Wired into index.html.tpl via postinst +
      an interest-noawait dpkg trigger (re-injected on pve-manager upgrades),
      removed on package removal via prerm; `make install` does the same for
      source installs. Fields track the plugin's properties()/options().
    - The opt-in SCSI-3 PR systemd units (qemu-pr-helper.socket/.service),
      installed DISABLED (dh_installsystemd --no-enable --no-start); enable the
      socket per node only when using persistent_reservations.
    - storage.cfg + multipath config examples under the package doc dir.
    Still deferred: the hitachiblock-repl replication CLI (it is coupled to the
    reference's old module layout and needs a rewrite against the FCLU internals).

